"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-06-26-nbc-brings-ai-version-legendary-broadcaster-olympic-coverage\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"SAN FRANCISCO, United States (AFP) - US media giant NBCUniversal on Wednesday announced that it will use the AI version of a legendary sports broadcaster to narrate personalised daily recaps of Olympic game events.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\", \"score\": 0.9474433078018266, \"rank\": 0.05309768701192878, \"text\": \"SAN FRANCISCO\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\"}, {\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 28, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999480597536391, \"rank\": 4.862042557722675e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 37, \"end\": 39, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9968655458575764, \"rank\": 0.0016312926286401823, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 52, \"end\": 64, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.5897019673681092, \"rank\": 0.6956323180601643, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 109, \"end\": 111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999997581981298, \"rank\": 2.3710882199707244e-07, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Narration by Hall of Fame announcer Al Michaels generated using artificial intelligence will voice the recaps that will be personalized to individual viewers of NBC's Peacock streaming service.\", \"from\": 216, \"to\": 409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 252, \"end\": 263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Michaels\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.682108291759924e-27, \"text\": \"Al Michaels\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Michaels\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Michaels\"}, {\"begin\": 377, \"end\": 380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 0.7442138307310908, \"rank\": 0.3283181862326984, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well-known broadcaster Michaels has worked a combined nine Olympic Games for NBC Sports and ABC Sports during his career, according to NBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 559, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 488, \"end\": 498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9994516220393925, \"rank\": 0.0005408481269186642, \"text\": \"NBC Sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 503, \"end\": 513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN_on_ABC\", \"score\": 0.9986128604362288, \"rank\": 0.0008206569547375376, \"text\": \"ABC Sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN_on_ABC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN_on_ABC\"}, {\"begin\": 546, \"end\": 558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.5897019673681092, \"rank\": 0.6956323180601643, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When I was approached about this, I was skeptical but obviously curious,\\\" Michaels said in a release.\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Then I saw a demonstration detailing what they had in mind.\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I said, 'I am in.'\\\"\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 745, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The AI was trained on the voice of Michaels along with his past appearances on NBC broadcasts, according to the company.\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 867, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 751, \"end\": 753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999997581981298, \"rank\": 2.3710882199707244e-07, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 826, \"end\": 829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 0.7442138307310908, \"rank\": 0.3283181862326984, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are bringing the best of sports together with the\\u202fbest of technology\\u202f to deliver fans a personalized Olympics experience in a way that's never been possible before,\\\" Peacock president Kelly Campbell said in the release.\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 1092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1057, \"end\": 1071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Campbell\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kelly Campbell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Campbell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Campbell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The collaboration with Michaels comes as musicians, actors, and others whose livelihoods depend on their likenesses or voices strive to make sure AI models are not trained on such material without their permission.\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1240, \"end\": 1242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999997581981298, \"rank\": 2.3710882199707244e-07, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBCUniversal estimated that nearly 7 million different personalised versions of the daily Olympic recap could be streamed across the United States during the Olympic Games in Paris.\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1310, \"end\": 1322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.5897019673681092, \"rank\": 0.6956323180601643, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 1443, \"end\": 1456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999480597536391, \"rank\": 4.862042557722675e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1485, \"end\": 1490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999946987827114, \"rank\": 5.30124534049349e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The technology will mine NBC Sports clips to create daily playlists showcasing top moments from the prior 24 hours and tease what is in store for the day ahead.\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1518, \"end\": 1528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9994516220393925, \"rank\": 0.0005408481269186642, \"text\": \"NBC Sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A team of NBCUniversal editors will review all the content for accuracy and quality assurance, the company said.\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1665, \"end\": 1677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.5897019673681092, \"rank\": 0.6956323180601643, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC and Peacock will present live coverage of the Olympic Games, starting with the opening ceremony on July 26.\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1880, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1769, \"end\": 1772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 0.7442138307310908, \"rank\": 0.3283181862326984, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}, {\"begin\": 1777, \"end\": 1784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9998882074313574, \"rank\": 0.00011180485986517918, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1893, \"entities\": []}]}"